#-1. Create a git account 
#	https://github.com/join

0. Download git and install
	apt-get install git

0.1 Start git repository
	git init <repo name>
	 
	or

0.1 Clone (Download) git repository
	git clone <url>

#0.2 (optional) Config git
#	git config --global user.name "<user name>"
#	git config --global user.email "<user email>" 
#	tip: quotation marks ("") are needed

1. Check for updates
	#you need to do it everytime you start work, it will sync you with remote repo
	#you dont have to do it if you started your local git repo right now
	git pull <url>

2. Do something
#	you dont have to but you should
#	¯\_(ツ)_/¯

3. Add your trash-code to stages
	git add -A
#	try git add -A --verbose

4. Commit
	git commit -m "explain what you have done"
#	explain or give a good title, remember you cant remember your code one week later
#	imagine a stranger reading your code, will he/she understand?

5. Push (Harder)
	git push <variable name> master
#	type your user name and password
#	great! Now your code is online to embarrass you! Perfect 1/10

